# NestJS architecture

Follow `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` and `docs/CODING_STANDARDS.md`. Prefer NestJS-idiomatic patterns over generic Express/Node style.

## Layering

- **Controllers** — routing and I/O only. No Prisma. No business logic.
- **Services** — business logic, `prisma.$transaction`, domain events.
- **Cross-module side effects** — `@nestjs/event-emitter`, not direct service coupling for “order paid → email/notification” style work.
- **Module boundaries** — feature modules under `src/modules/*` talk only through exported services. Never reach into another module’s Prisma queries or controllers.

## Data access

- No repository layer over Prisma. Use the shared `PrismaService`.
- Complex queries live as private methods on the owning service.
- Abstractions gateways only when a second real implementation exists (e.g. payments).

## Responses

- Global response envelope wraps every success/error. Controllers return bare data; do not hand-roll `{ status, message, data }` shapes.
